# Known-good DEPLOYED binary baseline for `west darling-doctor` check 3.
#
# These are the md5s of the last-known-good deployed closure binaries in the install prefix. The
# doctor compares the deployed dyld (both copies) / mldr / darlingserver against these by default.
#
# Format: one "key = md5" per line; '#' comments. Keys: dyld, mldr, dserver.
# UPDATE this file (and note why + which Bead) whenever a legitimate rebuild changes what is
# deployed — otherwise the doctor will (correctly) flag the new deploy as a baseline mismatch.
#
# Current baseline: the prod-matched set restored after perf#24c2* work
#   dyld    79b22273  (dyld-733.6, boot-compatible with the deployed 06-15 closure)
#   mldr    f0cd2a82  (perf#21b compact-fd band)
#   dserver 835946f9  (perf#18 ring transport)

dyld    = 79b22273481ea61ab63c0606c23ab300
mldr    = f0cd2a82efc4cb4614b63cabac0168f8
dserver = 835946f9df06f3902581e2e66f3c08e7
